    "Reaction time and accuracy were first analyzed as a function of congruency alone. A second analysis was completed for these variables as a function of both congruency and direction. \n",
    "\n",
    "## Reaction Time \n",
    "\n",
    "Reaction times were longer in incongruent trials (*M* = 571.28 ms) than in congruent trials (*M* = 477.41 ms) across both directions. A one-way repeated-measures ANOVA revealed a significant main effect of congruency on reaction time (`{python} rt1_stat`), with longer reaction times in incongruent trials. A 2 x 2 repeated measures ANOVA revealed a significant main effect of congruency on reaction time (`{python} rt2_cong_stat`). There was no significant main effect of direction (`{python} rt2_dir_stat`) and no significant interaction between congruency and direction (`{python} rt2_int_stat`). The results for the reaction time of congruent trials compared to the incongruent trials are depicted in @fig-rt."
